      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Absolutely, you can try to limit your exposure, which is a very smart move. You can negotiate to limit the indemnification to only claims that arise from your *negligence* or a *breach of your specific obligations*. You could also try to cap the total amount you have to pay out. It's important to be specific, so instead of \"all claims,\" you might suggest limiting it to \"claims arising directly from your willful misconduct.\"",
      "source": "target",
